      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Apologies for the confusion. The indemnification clause in the NDA means that if you, as the Recipient, violate the agreement or if your representatives act negligently or with willful misconduct, you are responsible for covering all the costs and damages that the Disclosing Party might incur as a result. This includes any legal fees, settlements, judgments, and other expenses. Essentially, you are agreeing to protect the Disclosing Party from any financial fallout that may occur due to your actions or those of your representatives. It's a way to ensure that the Disclosing Party is not left to bear the burden of any negative consequences that arise from the agreement.",
